data.title: Ola Rapace - Ethnicity of Celebs
data.text:
Birth Name: Pär Ola Norell

Place of Birth: Tyresö, Stockholms län, Sweden

Date of Birth: 3 December, 1971

Ethnicity: Swedish

Ola Rapace is a Swedish actor.

He is the son of Britta Margareta and Jan Olof Norell, who are academics. He has a daughter with his former partner, actress Malin Morgan; and a son with his former wife, actress Noomi Rapace. They both selected Rapace as their stage surname. The word means “bird of prey” in Spanish and Italian.

Ola’s paternal grandfather was Olof Harald Norell (the son of Gunnar Norell and Hulda Eugenia Elisabet Petersson). Olof was born in Säter. Gunnar was the son of Per Reinhold Norell and Josefina Augusta Karolina Söderling. Hulda was the daughter of Benjamin Petersson and Johanna Kristina Andreasdotter.

Ola’s paternal grandmother was Siv Margit Elvira Berenheim (the daughter of Erik Adolf Ture Berenheim and Agnes Elvira Asplund). Margit) was born in Kila, Södermanland. Ture was born in Tybble, the son of Johan Eric Carlsson and Johanna Mathilda Hellqvist. Agnes was the daughter of Fredric August Asplund and Anna Sofia Petersson.

Ola’s maternal grandfather was John Evald Jonsson (the son of Anders Johan Jonsson and Anna Kathrina, later Katarina, Jonsson). John Evald was born in Österfärnebo, Västernorrland. Anders Johan was the son of Jonas (later Jon) Olsson and Sara Andersdotter. Anna Katarina was the daughter of Pehr (later Per) Olof Jonsson and Johanna Jonsdotter.

Ola’s maternal grandmother was Vivan Elsa Linnéa Stein (the daughter of Henrik Stein and Gerda Linnéa Petersson). Vivan was born in Mjölby, Östergötland. Henrik was the son of August Karlsson Stein and Emma Christina Hallberg. Gerda was the daughter of Frans Gustaf Petersson and Johanna Johansdotter.
